Milt, 
The brass inlay groups you mention did not use any sort of clear coat.  If present, that would be a recent addition, probably to try to &quot;improve&quot; the surface of a rusty plate and/or to try to hold loose inlay in place.  I doubt that it&#39;s lacquer - it&#39;s probably something modern.  I&#39;d consider it a serious condition problem.  I have seen that occasionally on Onin tsuba, which do tend to have very dry, rusty plates that are very difficult to restore properly.

Agreed that nikuoki is a different term when used around swords.

Jim  

